                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/2035: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom (<persName type="to"
                        >Winant</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-26T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 26, 1942—midnight.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>860. Your 845, February 22, midnight. The American Government will be glad to
                    associate itself with the British Government in the plans for the relief of
                    Greece as outlined in Mr. Eden’s letter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
